SCHNEIDER v. FINKELSTEIN. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, First Department. June 11, 1909.) Action by Charles Schneider against Morris F. Finkelstein.

Witt this case has been consolidated in this court cases bearing titles as follows: Monro G. Dessauer v. John B. Sagarra; Henry Erkins v. John Tucker; Frederick Engelhardt v. James T. Fargo; Joseph Kirschner v. Fourteenth Street Store.

No opinions. Applications de nied, with $10 costs in each case. Order: signed. See, also, 107 N. Y. Supp. 126; 61 Misc. Rep. 495, 115 N. Y. Supp. 256.
